title: Study of the 14C(p,n)14N and 14C(a,n)17-O reactions

x4freetext: Experiment performed at the Wisconsin
electrostatic generator.
Target prepared by high-frequency
discharge in acetylene at a pressure of about 0.7 mm
Hg between electrodes containing the 10-mil tungsten
target backings spaced 1 cm apart. The acetylene was
converted from barium carbonate enriched to 38.7% in
14C. Deposit of unknown composition, which turned
dark brown upon heating in air to 400 deg C and black
upon bombardment was assumed to be carbon of the same
isotopic constitution as the barium carbonate.
Compiled by S.H.
Data taken from fig.4 of the reference
Long counter based on a BF3 proportional
counter
